# Header

There is a UART connection between the fill cart and the Raspberry Pi on the fill cart

However, the Raspberry pi works with 3.3 v and the arduino works with 5v.

When Raspberry pi sends a message (with tx pin GPIO 14) to the arduino arduino (arduino recieves on RX 0), it works ( the arduino can read a 3.3v signal). 


When arduino sends a 5v message (tx 1 on arduion) to the raspberry pi (on GPIO15 rx pin). It doesn't work. We can't send 5v on the Raspberry Pi!! We need a voltage divider
